TopicTitle: Keep getting hard crash to desktop

Articles.Content: Shortly put you are running out of RAM. Use texture reducers or uninstall some mods to bring your RAM usage under control.

Got the same issue. Plenty of mod installed. I have deleted B9 HX parts to help game engine with memory - I don't use those parts for now, so deleting those have made some RAM space for other mods. Also have installed ATM mod to reduce textures, that helps with large number of used mods.

By reducing installed parts I didn't get rid completely CTD, just pospone it. After several scene changes SPH/KSP/ship flight game still CTD at some point.

Looks like some kind of memory leaks, game engine need to dispose no longer needed objects (textures/parts) on scene changes, but fail to do that properly.

Failing to dispose unwanted objects always leeds to CTD at some point. Well, at least I know that I play game too much when CTD happens.
